- `Math.ceil` is used instead of subtracting 1 from `pageAmount` because if you divide `totalJobs` by `jobsPerPage`, you want to round up to the nearest whole number to ensure you have a page for any remainder jobs.
- The `new Array(pageAmount).fill('')` constructor creates an array of `pageAmount` length and fills it with empty strings which is more explicitly clear and concise.
