To loop through a list of links in an automation script like the one you've provided, you would usually use commands such as storing the list of links in an array, then iterating over them with a loop structure such as a `while` or `forEach` command, depending on the automation tool you're using.

Most automation tools don't directly support JavaScript logic, but they have their own set of commands for loops and data storage. Assuming you are using a tool that follows a Selenium IDE-like command structure, you would achieve looping through a list of links with a structure similar to the following JSON:

```json
{
  "Name": "Loop Through Links",
  "CreationDate": "2024-1-20",
  "Commands": [
    {
      "Command": "store",
      "Target": "0",
      "Value": "linkIndex",
      "Description": "Initialize link index"
    },
    {
      "Command": "storeJson",
      "Target": "[\"link1\", \"link2\", \"link3\"]",
      "Value": "linksArray",
      "Description": "Store the list of links in an array"
    },
    {
      "Command": "while",
      "Target": "${linkIndex} < ${linksArray}.length",
      "Value": "",
      "Description": "Start of loop through links"
    },
    {
      "Command": "echo",
      "Target": "Opening link number ${linkIndex+1}",
      "Value": "",
      "Description": "Log the current link being opened"
    },
    {
      "Command": "open",
      "Target": "${linksArray}[${linkIndex}]",
      "Value": "",
      "Description": "Open the link at the current index"
    },
    {
      "Command": "executeScript",
      "Target": "return Number(${linkIndex}) + 1;",
      "Value": "linkIndex",
      "Description": "Increment link index after opening a link"
    },
    {
      "Command": "end",
      "Target": "",
      "Value": "",
      "Description": "End of loop"
    }
  ]
}
```

You will need to replace `storeJson` and the appropriate link array with your actual links. The `while` command starts the loop, which continues as long as the condition `${linkIndex} < ${linksArray}.length` is true. Within the loop, the `open` command opens a link at the current index, and `linkIndex` is incremented after each link is processed. After all links are visited, the loop ends.

Please note that corrections have been made assuming the automation tool uses variables and commands similar to those of Selenium IDE. Modifications should be based on the specifics of the tool you're actually using.
